A MOTORCYCLIST is seriously ill in hospital after his bike was involved in a crash with a car this morning.
The accident happened at the junction of Oswald Street and the Broomielaw, near the Riverboat Casino in Glasgow.
Police Scotland said the 44-year-old man was taken to the city's Royal Infirmary where his condition is described as serious.
The driver of the car was uninjured.
A force spokesman said: “Police inquiries are ongoing to ascertain the circumstances surrounding the incident.”
Anyone who witnessed the accident, which happened around 11am, is asked to contact the non-emergency 101 number.
